<TITLE> All set for PM's oath Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 03 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangabhaban is ready to host the swearing-in of the Prime Minister-elect Sheikh Hasina and her cabinet on Tuesday, the cabinet secretary said. "The oath-taking ceremony of the new cabinet will take place at 6pm o Tuesday and we are taking all preparations," Md Abdul Aziz told bdnews24.com Saturday. President Iazuddin Ahmed will officiate at the swearing-in ceremony of the new cabinet at the Darbar Hall of the presidential palace. "Fifty cars are ready for the cabinet members and a guest list of more than 1000 has been finalised," Aziz said. Former presidents, former chief advisers, former speakers, former ministers, heads of different diplomatic missions, senior military officers, senior members of the media and top civil servants will be invited. All registered political parties will be given two invitation cards, but the two major partiesAL, BNPwill get more. bdnews
